In the MATTER OF Logan M. TERRY, an Attorney at Law (Attorney No. 007892003) D-147 September Term 2017
081316 Supreme Court of New Jersey. November 1, 2018

ORDER

The Disciplinary Review Board having filed with the Court its decision in DRB 17-417, concluding that Logan M. Terry of Cinnaminson, who was admitted to the bar of this State in 2003, should be censured for violating RPC 1.7 (a)(2) (conflict of interest) and RPC 8.4(d) (conduct prejudicial to the administration of justice, and good cause appearing;

It is ORDERED that Logan M. Terry is hereby censured; and it is further

ORDERED that the entire record of this matter be made a permanent part of respondent's file as an attorney at law of this State; and it is further

ORDERED that respondent reimburse the Disciplinary Oversight Committee for appropriate administrative costs and actual expenses incurred in the prosecution of this matter, as provided in Rule 1:20-17.
